- I WENT TO SCHOOL FOR IT.
I'M NOT KIDDING.

14:09.980 --> 14:11.561
OH, HEY THERE,
TONYA HARDING.

14:11.600 --> 14:13.113
- I'M A REALLY GOOD SKATER.
- UH-HUH.

14:13.160 --> 14:14.184
- AM I NOT
A REALLY GOOD SKATER?

14:14.230 --> 14:15.913
- NO, YOU ARE
A GOOD SKATER.

14:15.950 --> 14:17.577
YOU ONLY FELL ONCE.
- I ONLY FELL ONCE!

14:17.610 --> 14:19.430
AND IT WASN'T EVEN
A BAD FALL.

14:19.470 --> 14:21.358
IT WAS JUST
SOME FREAK ACCIDENT.

14:21.410 --> 14:23.571
I GOTTA GET CHECKED OUT
FOR OSTEOPOROSIS.

14:23.620 --> 14:26.236
HEY, DID MY DAD CALL
ABOUT MY OLD GOLF CLUBS FOR SYD?

14:26.270 --> 14:27.589
- I HAVEN'T HEARD.

14:27.620 --> 14:30.589
- WELL, SYD, DO YOU KNOW WHAT
WE ARE DOING TODAY?

14:30.620 --> 14:32.895
- TODAY'S MY PLAYDATE
WITH CHLOE.

14:32.940 --> 14:35.079
- MAYBE JUST THIS ONCE
WE CAN RESCHEDULE CHLOE,

14:35.110 --> 14:37.692
BECAUSE I HAVE
SOMETHING SO SPECIAL

14:37.730 --> 14:38.799
PLANNED FOR YOU AND ME.

14:38.840 --> 14:41.183
- WELL, I THOUGHT
WE HAD SPECIAL TIME YESTERDAY.

14:41.220 --> 14:44.257
AND THE DAY BEFORE THAT.
- RIGHT.

14:44.290 --> 14:46.463
WELL, TODAY
WE'RE GOING TO THE ZOO

14:46.500 --> 14:48.604
BECAUSE THEY HAVE
BABY KOMODO DRAGONS.

14:48.640 --> 14:50.016
- COOL!

14:50.060 --> 14:51.573
- GET YOUR BAG, LET'S GO.
- OKAY.

14:53.470 --> 14:55.222
- [chuckles]

14:59.650 --> 15:01.333
- IT'S A FACT THAT THINGS
GET OUT OF CONTROL

15:01.380 --> 15:02.688
ON PROM NIGHT,
AND I'M JUST ASKING YOU TO

15:02.720 --> 15:04.540
REALLY TALK TO HER, THAT'S ALL.
- I DID TALK TO HER.

15:04.590 --> 15:05.727
WE WENT OVER THE RULES
FOR PROM NIGHT,

15:05.760 --> 15:07.443
AND HER CURFEW'S
GONNA BE AN HOUR LATER,

15:07.490 --> 15:09.071
WHICH IS TOTALLY FINE.
- HONEY--

15:09.110 --> 15:10.520
- IF SHE WANTS TO GO
TO AN AFTER-PARTY, LET HER.

15:10.560 --> 15:11.652
- "IF" SHE WANTS
TO GO TO AN AFTER-PARTY?

15:11.700 --> 15:12.667
HONEY, THAT'S BEING NAIVE.

15:12.700 --> 15:14.622
- IT'S NOT BEING NAIVE.
- IT IS BEING NAIVE.

15:14.670 --> 15:15.807
HONEY, OF COURSE SHE'S
GONNA GO TO AN AFTER-PARTY.

15:15.840 --> 15:18.422
- I LAID OUT THE RULES.
- I HAD SEX WITH MICHELLE MCCANN

15:18.460 --> 15:20.087
ON PROM NIGHT.
- I KNOW YOU DID, OKAY?

15:20.120 --> 15:21.189
- OKAY.

15:21.230 --> 15:22.015
- BUT I HATE TO POINT
IT OUT TO YOU.

15:22.050 --> 15:23.153
KIDS ARE GONNA HAVE SEX
NO MATTER

15:23.190 --> 15:24.009
IF IT'S PROM NIGHT OR NOT.

15:24.060 --> 15:25.709
- NO, NO, NO, HONEY.
- YES, THEY ARE.

15:25.750 --> 15:26.819
- IT'S DIFFERENT. NO, IT'S NOT.
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.

15:26.850 --> 15:28.260
DO YOU KNOW WHAT I REMEMBER
ABOUT MY PROM NIGHT?

15:28.300 --> 15:29.710
- WHAT?
- NOTHING.

15:29.750 --> 15:31.194
ABSOLUTELY NOTHING.

15:31.240 --> 15:32.719
I DON'T REMEMBER
WHAT HER DRESS LOOKED LIKE.

15:32.750 --> 15:34.331
I DON'T REMEMBER
WHAT COLOR IT WAS.

15:34.380 --> 15:36.029
I DON'T REMEMBER
WHAT HER PARENTS LOOKED LIKE.

15:36.070 --> 15:37.992
I DON'T REMEMBER
WHERE I PUT THE CORSAGE.

15:38.040 --> 15:39.758
- OH, MY GOD, OKAY.
- HONEY, I WAS LIKE A ZOMBIE

15:39.800 --> 15:41.131
WITH ONE DIRECT IVE--

15:41.180 --> 15:42.624
TO GET
MICHELLE MCCANN'S DRESS OFF.

15:42.660 --> 15:44.969
- GREAT.
- I DO REMEMBER ONE THING.

15:45.010 --> 15:46.454
SHE HAD A DRESS
WITH A SLIT UP TO HERE.

15:46.490 --> 15:47.593
- I KNOW, I REMEMBER.
- UP TO HERE, HONEY.

15:47.630 --> 15:48.733
- I SAW THE PICTURES, I KNOW.

15:48.770 --> 15:50.351
- I'M DOWN ON MY KNEES,
TAKING OFF HER GARTER BELT.

15:50.390 --> 15:51.664
- I DON'T WANT TO HEAR THIS
RIGHT NOW.

15:51.700 --> 15:52.735
I DON'T WANT TO HEAR
WHAT YOU'RE SAYING.

15:52.770 --> 15:54.522
STOP.
- I WANT TO MAKE A POINT.

15:54.570 --> 15:55.776
I WANT YOU TO
REALLY TALK TO OUR DAUGHTER.

15:55.810 --> 15:57.220
- HADDIE
IS NOT MICHELLE MCCANN,

15:57.260 --> 15:59.057
AND I WILL TALK TO HER.

15:59.090 --> 16:02.674
- THANK YOU.

16:02.720 --> 16:04.267
[footsteps approaching]

16:04.300 --> 16:05.403
- HEY.
- HI.

16:05.440 --> 16:06.748
- CAN I TALK TO YOU
FOR A SECOND?

16:06.790 --> 16:08.678
- AH.
I WOULD LOVE TO

16:08.720 --> 16:10.585
BUT I'M WORKING,

16:10.620 --> 16:14.101
AND I'VE BEEN INSTRUCTED
TO PUT MYSELF FIRST.

16:14.140 --> 16:16.586
- OKAY, COULD YOU
PUT YOURSELF FIRST

16:16.630 --> 16:18.621
IN, LIKE, TWO MINUTES
AFTER WE TALK?

16:18.660 --> 16:21.720
I TRIED TO TALK TO ADAM,
BUT HE HATES MY GUTS.

16:21.770 --> 16:23.317
- SORRY, CROS.

16:23.360 --> 16:25.624
YOU DID SLEEP WITH
HIS CHILD'S BEHAVIORAL AIDE.

16:25.670 --> 16:27.661
- YEAH, IT SOUNDS SO SCANDALOUS
THE WAY YOU SAY IT.

16:27.710 --> 16:29.018
- NO, I KNOW.
IT'S DEFINITELY

16:29.050 --> 16:30.802
THE WAY IT SOUNDS
THAT WAS SCAN DALOUS

16:30.850 --> 16:32.158
'CAUSE DOING IT,
NO BIG DEAL.

16:32.190 --> 16:34.704
- SARAH, I'M NOT DENYING
WHAT A JERK I AM.

16:34.750 --> 16:37.298
I TAKE
FULL RESPONSIBILITY.

16:37.340 --> 16:39.808
I DON'T KNOW WHAT ELSE
YOU'D LIKE ME TO SAY.

16:39.860 --> 16:43.023
- I'M SORRY.
IT JUST PISSES ME OFF.

16:43.070 --> 16:45.709
- WELL, I--

16:45.760 --> 16:47.751
I CAME OVER BECAUSE

16:47.790 --> 16:48.893
I'M GONNA
SELL THE HOUSEBOAT,

16:48.930 --> 16:51.581
AND I'M GONNA USE THAT MONEY
TO PUT A DOWN PAYMENT

16:51.630 --> 16:53.621
ON A HOUSE
IN HOPES THAT

16:53.660 --> 16:55.764
JASMINE WILL WANT TO
COME LIVE IN IT WITH ME.

16:55.800 --> 16:57.620
- WHAT?

16:57.670 --> 17:00.662
YOU'RE GONNA BUY A HOUSE
SHE'S NEVER SEEN

17:00.700 --> 17:02.520
TO TRY TO WIN HER BACK?
- LOOK, I DON'T--

17:02.570 --> 17:03.776
I DON'T KNOW WHAT ELSE
TO DO.

17:03.810 --> 17:04.629
I WOULD DO ANYTHING.

17:04.670 --> 17:06.490
IF I THOUGHT
SHE WANTED AN AIRPLANE,

17:06.540 --> 17:08.360
I WOULD FIGURE OUT
HOW TO GET HER AN AIRPLANE.

17:08.400 --> 17:10.641
SO I THOUGHT
MAYBE YOU COULD COME BY

17:10.680 --> 17:12.819
AND GIVE ME, LIKE, YOU KNOW,
A FEMALE'S PERSPECTIVE

17:12.850 --> 17:15.569
ON WHETHER SHE'LL THINK
IT'S CUTE OR NICE,

17:15.620 --> 17:17.576
AND YOU KNOW,
IF SHE WOULD LIKE IT.

17:17.620 --> 17:19.759
- I'VE NEVER BOUGHT A HOUSE,

17:19.790 --> 17:21.678
BUT I AM A FEMALE.

17:21.730 --> 17:23.721
SO YES, I CAN DO THAT.

17:23.760 --> 17:25.375
- THANK YOU.

17:25.420 --> 17:26.796
- I DON'T KNOW
IF IT'LL WORK, BUT IT'S--

17:26.830 --> 17:29.105
IT'S A GRAND GESTURE.

17:29.150 --> 17:31.175
- IT'LL BE GREAT TOO
IF MAYBE, YOU KNOW,

17:31.220 --> 17:33.381
JULIA AND JOEL--
- YEAH, AND ADAM.

17:36.400 --> 17:39.289
- I DON'T THINK
ADAM'S EVER GONNA COME OVER.

17:47.540 --> 17:49.121
- WELL, I'LL BE THERE.

17:51.510 --> 17:54.399
- HEY, HONEY, I THINK WE SHOULD
TRY ON THE GREEN ONE FIRST.

17:54.450 --> 17:55.678
- I'M TRYING
ON THE PURPLE ONE.

17:55.720 --> 17:57.449
- FOUND A LITTLE BLUE ONE
THAT MIGHT WORK.

17:57.490 --> 17:59.515
- OKAY.
- IT'S A LOT SHORTER,

17:59.560 --> 18:01.175
BUT IT'S STILL
KINDA CUTE AND FLIRTY.

18:01.210 --> 18:03.178
IT'S A LITTLE SHORT,
THOUGH.

18:03.220 --> 18:05.768
HEY, HONEY, DID YOU GUYS
TALK ABOUT YOUR PLANS

18:05.800 --> 18:07.688
FOR AFTER PROM?

18:07.740 --> 18:09.492
- NO, I SAID
I WOULD CALL YOU, RIGHT?

18:09.530 --> 18:10.906
- I KNOW, BUT I JUST--
I NEED TO KNOW

18:10.950 --> 18:12.497
IF ANY OF YOUR FRIENDS
ARE GETTING HOTEL ROOMS,

18:12.530 --> 18:13.918
SO I KNOW WHERE TO
PICK YOU UP.

18:13.950 --> 18:15.702
- MOM, NO,
THEY'RE NOT, OKAY?

18:15.740 --> 18:17.742
- [gasp5]

18:17.780 --> 18:19.429
HONEY, YOU LOOK STUNNING.

18:19.470 --> 18:20.880
- NO.
- IT IS SO PRETTY.

18:20.920 --> 18:22.330
- I LOOK LIKE--
- I DIDN'T THINK THE PURPLE

18:22.370 --> 18:23.746
WOULD WORK,
BUT IT WORKS WITH THE JEWELS,

18:23.790 --> 18:25.439
AND IT'S LIKE
A YOUNG ELIZABETH TAYLOR.

18:25.480 --> 18:26.788
- NO, I DON'T.
I DON'T LIKE IT.

18:26.820 --> 18:29.892
- ARE YOU AND ALEX
TALKING ABOUT SEX?

18:30.970 --> 18:32.301
I JUST HAD TO ASK.

18:32.350 --> 18:34.489
- NO, MOM.

18:34.520 --> 18:35.726
- OKAY.

18:35.760 --> 18:37.830
OKAY, I JUST WONDERED.

18:37.870 --> 18:40.794
- PROM NIGHT IS A CLICHE NIGHT
TO HAVE SEX, OKAY?

18:40.840 --> 18:42.182
- I AGREE.
HONEY, AS A MOM, I JUST

18:42.220 --> 18:43.767
HAVE TO ASK THESE
QUESTIONS, I'M SORRY.

18:43.810 --> 18:45.459
- YEAH, WHATEVER.
IT'S COOL.

18:45.500 --> 18:47.149
- YOU LOOK AMAZING.

18:47.190 --> 18:50.421
I MEAN, I'M NOT KIDDING.
YOU LOOK STUNNING.

18:50.470 --> 18:51.630
- I'M GONNA
TRY ON SOMETHING ELSE.

18:51.680 --> 18:53.819
- ALL RIGHT.
TRY ON THE GREEN.

18:53.850 --> 18:55.294
THE DARK--

18:55.340 --> 18:58.332
I CAN...BRING IT IN.

19:00.820 --> 19:02.822
OKAY.

19:10.730 --> 19:13.597
- HEY.
- HEY.

19:13.630 --> 19:15.621
- THIS JUST IN...
I'M NOT COOKING.

19:15.670 --> 19:17.353
- I'M SO SURPRISED.

19:17.390 --> 19:20.325
- MEDIOCRE PIZZA
OR TRULY TERRIBLE CHINESE?

19:20.360 --> 19:22.419
- OOH, CHINESE, 'CAUSE
IT'S THE TONGUE TWISTER.

19:22.470 --> 19:23.607
- [chuckles]

19:23.640 --> 19:24.914
WHAT'S ALL THIS?

19:24.950 --> 19:27.430
- JUST A BUNCH
OF NANA'S OLD DRESSES.

19:27.470 --> 19:28.949
- OH, YEAH?
AW.

19:28.990 --> 19:32.949
WHAT FOR?
- WELL...DON'T LAUGH.

19:32.990 --> 19:34.309
PROM.

19:34.340 --> 19:35.955
- [laughing]

19:36.000 --> 19:38.400
- SEE, I TOLD YOU
NOT TO LAUGH IN MY FACE.

19:38.450 --> 19:40.680
- YOU'RE KIDDING!
- I'M NOT KIDDING.

19:40.730 --> 19:42.937
I CAN EXPLAIN,
SO IF YOU'LL HOLD

19:42.970 --> 19:45.245
YOUR HYSTERICAL LAUGHTER
UNTIL THE END.

19:45.280 --> 19:47.862
HADDIE AND HER BOYFRIEND ARE,
LIKE, BEGGING ME TO GO,

19:47.910 --> 19:51.619
AND SO I THOUGHT
IT WOULD BE FUNNY TO GO.

19:51.670 --> 19:53.945
AND YOU KNOW, WHATEVER.
- WHO IS YOUR DATE?

19:53.980 --> 19:55.971
- I DON'T KNOW.
SOME GUY THAT ALEX KNOWS

19:56.020 --> 19:57.840
FROM THE COMMUNITY CENTER.

19:57.880 --> 19:59.871
- YOU'RE GOING TO PROM
ON A BLIND DATE!

19:59.920 --> 20:02.741
IT'S, LIKE, 1954.
- SO WEIRD.

20:02.780 --> 20:04.987
IT'S STUPID.
- I MEAN, IT'S NOT STUPID.

20:05.030 --> 20:06.918
I LOVE IT.
I'M SO EXCITED!

20:06.960 --> 20:10.020
I MEAN, OF COURSE IT'S DUMB,
IT'S DORKY, IT'S CORNY.

20:10.070 --> 20:10.889
- IT IS.
- IT'S PROM.

20:10.930 --> 20:14.275
BUT IT'S A STORY
YOU'LL ALWAYS TELL.

20:14.310 --> 20:17.655
IT'S AN EXPERIENCE
YOU WON'T BE SORRY YOU HAD

20:17.690 --> 20:18.964
NO MATTER
IF IT'S GOOD OR BAD.

20:19.010 --> 20:22.832
AND IT'S JUST
A BEAUTIFUL, SENTIMENTAL WAY

20:22.870 --> 20:23.859
TO SAY GOOD-BYE
TO HIGH SCHOOL

20:23.910 --> 20:25.662
AND I LOVE
THAT YOU'RE DOING IT.

20:28.670 --> 20:30.592
SO WHAT, ARE YOU
GONNA CUT ONE OF THESE UP?

20:30.640 --> 20:33.325
REALLY, GIVE IT A PRETTY IN PINK
KIN DA TREATMENT?

20:33.370 --> 20:34.917
DON'T ACT LIKE
YOU HAVEN'T SEEN IT.

20:34.950 --> 20:36.394
- YOU'RE DATING YOURSELF.

20:36.440 --> 20:37.816
- WELL, I HOPE
YOU'RE A LADIES MAN,

20:37.850 --> 20:40.364
BECAUSE THIS BOAT
IS A BIT OF A LURE

20:40.410 --> 20:42.059
FOR ATTRACTIVE LADIES.

20:42.100 --> 20:44.068
- SOUNDS SWEET.
- IT'S, UH...

20:44.100 --> 20:45.829
QUITE A VESSEL.
- SWEET.

20:45.860 --> 20:46.997
- BUCKLE UP.
- ALL RIGHT.

20:47.030 --> 20:48.440
- ALL RIGHT, MAN.

20:48.480 --> 20:49.754
UM, WHAT ELSE?
OH.

20:49.800 --> 20:51.825
I WOULDN'T KEEP
ANYTHING OUT HERE THAT RUSTS.

20:51.870 --> 20:53.553
THIS MIST IS REALLY DAMP.

20:53.590 --> 20:55.865
AND I'D KEEP THE MUSIC DOWN,

20:55.900 --> 20:57.936
'CAUSE IT
TRAVELS OVER THE WATER,

20:57.980 --> 20:59.766
AND THE NEIGHBORS
GET ANGRY.

20:59.810 --> 21:02.631
- OKAY.
- I THINK THAT'S IT.

21:02.670 --> 21:03.978
- ALL RIGHT.
- ALL RIGHT.

21:04.020 --> 21:05.772
- CAN I HAVE
MY HAND BACK NOW, OR--

21:05.810 --> 21:07.391
- OH, SORRY.

21:07.430 --> 21:08.874
OKAY, HERE ARE THE KEYS.

21:08.920 --> 21:10.672
ENJOY.

21:10.710 --> 21:12.917
AND CONGRATULATIONS.
- THANK YOU, MR. BRAVERMAN.

21:12.960 --> 21:14.882
- YEAH.

21:30.730 --> 21:31.901
- YOU HAVEN'T FINISHED
THE WORK!

21:31.940 --> 21:33.009
- I CAN'T FINISH--

21:33.050 --> 21:34.802
- YOU'VE GOT A CHARACTER
WITH NO DIGNITY.

21:34.840 --> 21:36.523
YOU'VE GOTTA
GIVE BARRY SOME DIGNITY.

21:36.570 --> 21:37.901
- I WILL GIVE
BARRY SOME DIGNITY.

21:37.950 --> 21:40.396
I'VE BEEN WORKING ON HIS DIGN--
- I NEED THE REWRITE.

21:40.430 --> 21:41.988
- I NEED TWO--
- YOU SAID TWO WEEKS!

21:42.020 --> 21:43.806
- TICK-TOCK, TICK-TOCK.
- IT'S MY DAUGHTER'S PROM!

21:43.850 --> 21:45.465
- OH, PROM!

21:45.510 --> 21:46.909
PROM!
I HATE THAT WORD.

21:46.960 --> 21:48.712
WHAT DO YOU WANT TO BE,
A SOCCER MOM?

21:48.750 --> 21:50.126
- I HATE THAT WORD.
SOCCER MOM.

21:50.170 --> 21:52.377
WHAT DOES THAT EVEN MEAN?
THAT'S THE LAST THING I AM.

21:52.410 --> 21:53.718
I'M A PERSON WHO'S A MOM

21:53.760 --> 21:55.091
WHO'S TRYING
TO GET SOME WRITING DONE.

21:55.140 --> 21:57.893
DO YOU HAVE KIDS?
- NO, NO, I DON'T HAVE KIDS.

21:57.930 --> 22:00.069
I HAVE WIVES.
I COLLECT WIVES.

22:00.110 --> 22:01.418
- HOW WONDERFUL.
WHAT NUMBER IS THAT?

22:01.450 --> 22:05.102
- THIS?
OH, THAT'S...

22:05.150 --> 22:08.313
THAT'S THE RING OF
MY FIRST WIFE.

22:14.540 --> 22:17.111
- I TAKE THIS SERIOUSLY.

22:17.160 --> 22:18.912
I'M KILLING MYSELF
OVER THIS THING.

22:18.950 --> 22:20.463
I'VE NEVER WORKED SO HARD.
- [chuckles]

22:20.510 --> 22:22.057
- I WILL STAY UP ALL NIGHT
TONIGHT TO FINISH

22:22.090 --> 22:24.365
WHAT WE STARTED,
BUT I HAVE TO GO.

22:24.410 --> 22:26.549
- HAVE A GREAT PROM.
- OH, GOD.

22:26.580 --> 22:28.502
- HAVE A WONDERFUL PROM.

22:28.550 --> 22:29.926
YOU DON'T
HAVE A WONDERFUL PLAY.

22:29.960 --> 22:33.168
- I HAVE A LIFE!
- YOU DON'T YET.

22:33.210 --> 22:34.689
SEAT BELTS!

22:34.730 --> 22:36.061
SEAT BELTS!

22:36.110 --> 22:38.135
- SO WHICH DRESS
DID HADDIE CHOOSE?

22:38.180 --> 22:39.169
THE PURPLE ONE?

22:39.210 --> 22:41.451
- SHE PICKED THE, LIKE,
MAUVEY-TAUPEY COLOR ONE.

22:41.490 --> 22:42.832
IT'S CUTE.
- DAD, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

22:42.870 --> 22:44.110
I TOLD YOU,
WE'RE NOT DRINKING TONIGHT.

22:44.150 --> 22:45.139
- HOW COME?
- BECAUSE I TOLD YOU,

22:45.190 --> 22:46.669
ALEX IS
A RECOVERING ALCOHOLIC.

22:46.710 --> 22:48.041
- I BET SHE LOOKS BEAUTIFUL.
- YEAH, WELL,

22:48.090 --> 22:50.399
SO WHAT'S HE GONNA DO,
ATTACK ME AND STEAL MY BEER?

22:50.430 --> 22:51.670
HE'S THE ALCOHOLIC, NOT ME.

22:51.710 --> 22:53.598
DID YOU TALK TO CROSBY,
BY THE WAY?

22:53.640 --> 22:55.016
- NO, I HAVEN'T.
COULD YOU JUST BACK OFF?

22:55.060 --> 22:57.642
- BACK OFF?
- IT WAS JUST LIKE YESTERDAY

22:57.680 --> 22:59.989
THAT WE WENT TO YOUR PROM,
ADAM, REMEMBER?

23:00.030 --> 23:03.090
WITH THE BEAUTIFUL
MOLLY MCCANN.

23:03.140 --> 23:04.539
- HER NAME WAS MICHELLE,
BUT--

23:04.590 --> 23:05.443
- WAS IT MICHELLE?

23:05.480 --> 23:07.163
I THOUGHT IT WAS MOLLY.
- MOLLY MCCANN.

23:07.210 --> 23:09.417
- DAD, REALLY, DO YOU MIND?
- HE WAS SO GA-GA OVER HER.

23:09.450 --> 23:11.099
[doorbell rings]
I WONDER WHAT HAPPENED TO HER?

23:11.140 --> 23:12.869
- I WONDER.
- DO YOU MIND?

23:12.900 --> 23:14.902
- WELL...HEY.
- I DIDN'T MISS IT, DID I?

23:14.940 --> 23:16.077
- NO!
- I'M LATE, I KNOW.

23:16.110 --> 23:17.975
HI, HOW ARE YOU?
- I'M GOOD.

23:18.010 --> 23:20.069
- I'M IRRATIONALLY
EXCITED ABOUT THIS.

23:20.120 --> 23:21.599
- GOOD, SO AM I.

23:21.640 --> 23:22.834
THEY'RE UPSTAIRS
GETTING READY.

23:22.880 --> 23:24.017
- OKAY.
IT'S ALL BECAUSE OF HADDIE

23:24.050 --> 23:26.462
THAT SHE'S EVEN GOING.
- WELL, SHE WANTED HER TO GO.

23:26.500 --> 23:27.979
- I KNOW, BUT SHE DOESN'T--
- HEY, SARAH!

23:28.020 --> 23:29.578
- SISTER SARAH.
- YEAH, I AM TOO.

23:29.610 --> 23:31.157
- DO YOU REMEMBER
YOUR PROM?

23:31.200 --> 23:32.713
WE WERE JUST
TALKING ABOUT ADAM'S PROM.

23:32.750 --> 23:33.887
- YEAH, JUST
RIGHT DOWN MEMORY LANE.

23:33.920 --> 23:36.434
- DO I REMEMBER MY PROM?
I SANG THE PROM THEME WITH SETH.

23:36.480 --> 23:37.993
LOVE LIFTS US UP
WHERE WE BELONG.

23:38.030 --> 23:39.679
- WHERE THE EAGLES FLY.
- THE EAGLES FLY, YOU KNOW?

23:39.720 --> 23:40.823
- I LIKE THAT SONG.

23:40.860 --> 23:43.033
- YES, AND HER HAIR
WAS REALLY UP.

23:43.070 --> 23:44.241
- YEAH.
IT WAS THE '805, MOM.

23:44.280 --> 23:45.827
WE HAD TO GO BIG.

23:45.870 --> 23:47.098
- LOOKED LIKE BRIDE
OF FRANKENSTEIN.

23:47.140 --> 23:48.721
- THANKS. THAT'S WHAT
I WAS KINDA GOING FOR.

23:48.770 --> 23:50.795
[doorbell rings]
KIND OF A SHEENA EASTON HOMAGE.

23:50.840 --> 23:52.808
[chatter continues]

23:52.840 --> 23:54.068
- HI.
- HEY.

23:54.120 --> 23:55.041
- HEY.
- HOW YOU DOING, MR. BRAVERMAN?

23:55.080 --> 23:56.047
- HOW ARE YOU, ALEX?
- HOW ARE YOU DOING?

23:56.080 --> 23:58.150
- YOU LOOK HANDSOME
IN YOUR TUXEDO THERE.

23:58.190 --> 23:59.600
- THANK YOU, THANK YOU.
- HI.

23:59.640 --> 24:01.119
- BRANDON.
- BRANDON?

24:01.160 --> 24:02.468
I'M ADAM BRAVERMAN,
COME ON IN.

24:02.510 --> 24:03.989
- HEY, THERE.
I'M SARAH.

24:04.020 --> 24:05.055
I'M AMBER'S MOM.

24:05.090 --> 24:07.194
- WHOA, WHOA.
[laughing]

24:07.230 --> 24:09.164
- NICE TO MEET YOU.
- SO NICE TO MEET YOU.

24:09.200 --> 24:10.883
- HEY, HOW YOU DOING?
- KRISTINA.

24:10.930 --> 24:12.545
- GOODNESS, YOU LOOK SO NICE.
- THANK YOU.

24:12.580 --> 24:13.820
- I'M ZEEK BRAVERMAN,
HOW DO YOU DO?

24:13.860 --> 24:14.827
- BRANDON.

24:14.860 --> 24:16.088
- HUH?
- BRANDON.

24:16.140 --> 24:17.129
- BRANDON.
- YEAH.

24:17.170 --> 24:18.797
- BRANDON, BRANDON.
- [chuckles]

24:18.830 --> 24:19.899
- THEY'RE GONNA BE DOWN
IN A MINUTE.

24:19.940 --> 24:21.202
- LET ME GET
A SHOT OF YOU GUYS.

24:21.250 --> 24:22.069
- YOU GUYS GET TOGETHER.

24:22.110 --> 24:23.725
PUT YOUR ARM
AROUND EACH OTHER THERE.

24:23.770 --> 24:25.032
YOUR HEADS TOGETHER THERE.
- GREAT.

24:25.080 --> 24:26.149
- GET YOU BOTH THERE.
- READY?

24:26.180 --> 24:27.977
- LUCKY GIRLS, HUH?
- CHEESE.

24:28.010 --> 24:29.637
- CHEESE.
- FANTASTIC.

24:29.670 --> 24:31.661
LOOK THIS WAY, BRANDON.
THERE YOU GO.

24:31.710 --> 24:33.109
- VERY CUTE.
I THINK YOU BLINKED.

24:33.160 --> 24:34.604
- A LITTLE CLOSER,
LITTLE CLOSER.

24:34.640 --> 24:36.187
- YOU HAD YOUR EYES
CLOSED THERE, ALEX.

24:36.230 --> 24:38.607
- HEY, WE--
- [gasp5]

24:38.640 --> 24:40.221
- HOLY MACKEREL!

24:40.270 --> 24:42.295
- WOW, LOOK AT THIS.
YOU LOOK VERY NICE.

24:42.340 --> 24:44.888
- OH, MY GOSH!
- LET ME CAPTURE THAT MOMENT

24:44.930 --> 24:47.091
RIGHT THERE.
- YOU GIRLS LOOK BEAUTIFUL.

24:47.140 --> 24:48.755
- WOW!
- YOU GIRLS!

24:48.790 --> 24:50.098
- THIS IS AS GOOD AS IT GETS.
- YOU LOOK VERY NICE.

24:50.140 --> 24:51.653
- LET'S GO FOR IT.
- TAKE SOME PICTURES.

24:51.690 --> 24:53.066
- YEAH, YEAH.

24:53.110 --> 24:54.759
- HOW'S IT GOING?
THANKS.

24:54.800 --> 24:57.109
- I KINDA WANT TO WEAR THIS,
BUT I THINK IT'S FOR YOU.

24:57.150 --> 24:59.072
- WE COULD TRADE OFF.
[glggleSJ

24:59.110 --> 25:02.216
- YOU ARE SMOKIN'.
YOU ARE AMAZING.

25:02.250 --> 25:03.217
COME HERE.

25:03.260 --> 25:05.251
- [giggIeSJ
- ALL RIGHT.

25:05.290 --> 25:06.973
- ALL RIGHT, YOU GUYS
KINDA GROUP TOGETHER?

25:07.020 --> 25:08.089
JUST SQUISH TOGETHER THERE?

25:08.120 --> 25:08.984
- THERE YOU GO.

25:09.020 --> 25:11.181
- GET TOGETHER.
- AMBER, LOOK THIS WAY.

25:11.230 --> 25:12.629
- WHERE ARE WE LOOKING?
- THAT'S GOOD.

25:12.680 --> 25:14.261
EVERYBODY SAY "PROM."
- ONE, TWO, THREE.

25:14.300 --> 25:16.291
- CHEESE.
all: PROM.

25:17.790 --> 25:21.886
[indistinct chatter]

25:33.670 --> 25:36.241
- YEAH, IT'S NICE.
THANK YOU.

25:49.300 --> 25:50.813
- STOP IT.

25:53.690 --> 25:56.784
[indistinct chatter
continues]

25:56.830 --> 25:58.991
HI, MOM.
- JUST--

25:59.040 --> 26:01.031
JUST CHECKING.

26:03.280 --> 26:05.248
- [laughing]

26:05.280 --> 26:06.588
- THANK YOU.
- BYE.

26:06.630 --> 26:07.904
- LOVE YOU TOO.
BYE.

26:07.940 --> 26:10.625
LOVE YOU.
- [glggleSJ

26:10.670 --> 26:11.807
- SEE YA.
- BYE, I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

26:11.840 --> 26:12.829
- LET'S GO.
- YOUNG MAN...

26:12.880 --> 26:13.949
- PUT IT ON STRAIGHT.
- OKAY.

26:13.980 --> 26:15.140
- ENJOY YOURSELF.
- I WILL, I WILL.

26:15.190 --> 26:17.249
- ...STRAIGHT AND NARROW.
SORRY.

26:17.290 --> 26:19.941
HAVE A GREAT TIME, BRANDON.
NICE TO MEET YOU.

26:19.990 --> 26:22.015
[engine turns,
car door closes]

26:31.690 --> 26:32.782
- AMBER AND HADDIE
OFF TO THE PROM TOGETHER.

26:32.830 --> 26:34.718
- I PRACTICALLY
FELL OUT OF MY CHAIR

26:34.760 --> 26:36.273
WHEN SHE SAID
SHE WANTED TO GO.

26:36.310 --> 26:38.346
AND WITH
A GUY SHE'S NEVER MET!

26:38.380 --> 26:39.768
- YEAH.
- GOOD FOR HER.

26:39.800 --> 26:41.210
THEY'LL HAVE FUN.

26:41.250 --> 26:45.903
UM...YOU KNOW,
CROSBY CAME TO SEE ME.

26:45.940 --> 26:47.828
- WELL, GOOD FOR HIM.
- HE WANTS US ALL

26:47.880 --> 26:49.188
TO COME LOOK AT THE HOUSE
TOMORROW.

26:49.220 --> 26:50.733
- YEAH, I KNOW.

26:50.780 --> 26:51.974
LOOK, SARAH,
WE'RE A BUNCH OF ADULTS.

26:52.020 --> 26:53.157
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
WE'RE SUPPOSED TO DO HERE.

26:53.190 --> 26:55.636
HELP HIM
PICK OUT CURTAINS?

26:55.680 --> 26:57.159
DO HIM A FAVOR
AND KEEP HIM FROM DOING

26:57.200 --> 26:59.088
AN INCREDIBLY STUPID THING,
WHICH HE'S DOING IN RESPONSE

26:59.130 --> 27:01.098
TO ANOTHER INCREDIBLY
STUPID THING THAT HE DID?

27:01.130 --> 27:03.405
WHICH, BY THE WAY,
CAN'T BE UNDONE.

27:03.440 --> 27:06.409
SO I DON'T--
I DON'T CARE.

27:06.450 --> 27:08.759
- SO YOU'RE NOT GONNA
COME SEE THE HOUSE TOMORROW?

27:08.790 --> 27:10.963
- NO.

27:11.000 --> 27:13.719
- YEAH, IT MIGHT BE A REALLY
STUPID THING HE'S DOING.

27:13.770 --> 27:16.762
AND IT ALSO MIGHT NOT WORK.

27:16.800 --> 27:18.836
JASMINE MIGHT NEVER
FORGIVE HIM.

27:18.870 --> 27:22.112
BUT WE
DON'T HAVE THAT OPTION.

27:22.150 --> 27:23.879
I HATE WHAT HE DID.

27:23.910 --> 27:26.253
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
LIKE IT EITHER.

27:26.290 --> 27:29.293
YOU CAN BE MAD AT HIM
AS LONG AS YOU WANT.

27:31.230 --> 27:34.222
HE'S...IN PAIN
AND HE NEEDS US.

27:34.270 --> 27:36.329
HE'S OUR BROTHER.

27:36.370 --> 27:39.373
JUST SHOW UP.

27:48.010 --> 27:51.969
[upbeat pop music]

27:52.010 --> 27:53.147
- OKAY, READY?
- READY.

27:53.180 --> 27:54.169
- I'LL TRY NOT TO FALL,

27:54.220 --> 27:56.495
BUT YOU HAVE TO TAKE ME
TO THE HOSPITAL IF I DO.

27:56.530 --> 27:58.737
- OKAY.
- OKAY, READY?

27:58.780 --> 28:00.736
OH, IT'S GONNA BE A GOOD ONE.
- THAT WAS A GREAT ONE.

28:00.780 --> 28:02.463
- I'M GONNA PUT THAT
UP IN MY ROOM.

28:02.500 --> 28:04.388
WRITE ABOUT IT IN MY DIARY.
- ON THE WALL OF SHAME.

28:04.440 --> 28:05.953
- LOOK AT THIS,
IT'S SO ELEGANT.

28:05.990 --> 28:07.298
IT'S LIKE
WE'RE REALLY IN PARIS.

28:07.340 --> 28:08.910
- OUI, OUI.
- THE MUSIC--

28:08.960 --> 28:10.882
[giggIeSJ
- CAN I TAKE YOUR COAT?

28:10.930 --> 28:12.716
- IT'S A SWEATER.
BUT, YEAH, I GUESS.

28:12.760 --> 28:13.920
- OKAY,
WHAT DO I DO WITH THIS NOW?

28:13.960 --> 28:15.473
- THIS IS AMAZING.

28:15.520 --> 28:17.476
- THESE STARS ARE AMAZING.

28:17.520 --> 28:19.101
IT WAS A GOOD TOUCH.

28:19.140 --> 28:20.823
- YEAH.
- THEY LOOK BEAUTIFUL.

28:20.870 --> 28:22.064
- OKAY, THANK YOU.

28:22.110 --> 28:23.964
- YOU KNOW WHAT
LOOKS BETTER THAN THAT?

28:24.010 --> 28:24.908
- WHAT?

28:24.940 --> 28:27.829
- YOU.

28:29.120 --> 28:30.519
- YOU LOOK OKAY.

28:30.570 --> 28:32.049
- JUST--JUST OKAY?

28:32.080 --> 28:35.322
- I MEAN, YEAH, KIND OF.
LIKE--

28:35.360 --> 28:38.249
- GIRL, I WAS BORN TO ROCK
THIS TUX AND YOU KNOW IT.

28:38.300 --> 28:40.393
- OKAY, WELL--
OH, HEY, GUYS.

28:40.440 --> 28:43.159
- SO GOOD WHEN YOU LOOK
LIKE YOU SHOULD

28:43.200 --> 28:45.885
WHEN YOU COME OUT TO PLAY
ALL THE PEOPLE SAY

28:45.930 --> 28:48.069
[doorbell rings]

28:48.100 --> 28:49.374
- UH-OH.
- HI.

28:49.410 --> 28:50.854
- HERE'S TROUBLE.
- HEY.

28:50.900 --> 28:52.128
- HOW ARE YOU?
- HEY, BUDDY.

28:52.170 --> 28:54.377
- LOOK AT WHAT
I FOUND IN MY GARAGE.

28:54.420 --> 28:55.967
- LOOK AT THAT,
IT'S ALMOST A FULL SET.

28:56.010 --> 28:58.274
- YEAH, IT IS A FULL SET.

28:58.320 --> 29:00.038
- YOU GUYS WANT
SOMETHING TO DRINK?

29:00.080 --> 29:01.934
- YEAH, I'LL HAVE A BEER.
- BONJOUR!

29:01.980 --> 29:03.311
- HI.
- BONJOUR!

29:03.360 --> 29:04.839
- BONJOUR.
- BONJOUR.

29:04.880 --> 29:06.529
- HEY, JULIA, LOOK
WHAT I FOUND IN THE GARAGE.

29:06.570 --> 29:10.154
- OH, MY GOD!
SYD, ARE YOU EXCITED?

29:10.190 --> 29:12.010
THESE ARE YOUR NEW
GOLF CLUBS!

29:12.060 --> 29:13.948
THEY WERE MINE.

29:13.990 --> 29:15.981
- OH.

29:16.030 --> 29:17.577
- WE GET TO PLAY GOLF
TOGETHER!

29:17.610 --> 29:19.089
WELL, YOU KNOW,
I WILL TEACH YOU,

29:19.130 --> 29:21.166
AND YOU CAN PLAY.
- I DON'T LIKE GOLF.

29:21.200 --> 29:22.997
- OH, WELL, YOU
HAVEN'T TRIED IT YET.

29:23.030 --> 29:26.784
- WELL, IT'S JUST THAT
I DON'T REALLY WANT TO PLAY.

29:26.830 --> 29:29.207
- IT'S GONNA BE
OUR THING.

29:29.250 --> 29:31.036
THE THING
WE DO TOGETHER.

29:31.070 --> 29:33.903
- I THOUGHT
WE WERE LEARNING FRENCH.

29:33.940 --> 29:36.932
HOW MANY THINGS
DO WE HAVE TO DO TOGETHER?

29:42.360 --> 29:44.282
- WE DON'T HAVE TO
DO TOO MANY.

29:56.100 --> 29:57.067
- HEY, JOEL...

29:57.100 --> 30:00.092
WHAT'S GOING ON?

30:04.380 --> 30:07.269
- SO ALEX TOLD ME
YOU PLAY THE BONGOS OR--

30:07.320 --> 30:09.311
- NO, I DON'T PLAY THE BONGOS.

30:09.350 --> 30:11.830
I PLAY GUITAR, KIND OF.
- OH, GUITAR.

30:11.870 --> 30:13.212
- I DON'T PLAY THAT MUCH--
- AMBER.

30:14.570 --> 30:16.014
- HI.
- HEY.

30:16.050 --> 30:18.325
- HOW'S IT GOING?
- DO YOU KNOW TYLER?

30:18.360 --> 30:20.043
- YEAH, HEY.
- BRANDON.

30:20.090 --> 30:22.365
- IT'S NICE TO MEET YOU.
- HI, I'M CASSIE. HI.

30:25.090 --> 30:27.536
I'VE BEEN THINKING ABOUT YOU
LIKE A LOT RECENTLY.

30:27.580 --> 30:30.299
WE USED TO S.A.T.
TUTOR TOGETHER, SO...

30:30.340 --> 30:32.900
SHE SLAYED ME AT VOCAB.
- IT'S TRUE.

30:32.930 --> 30:34.204
- WHAT ENDED UP
HAPPENING WITH THAT?

30:34.240 --> 30:35.969
- WITH VOCAB?

30:36.000 --> 30:37.103
- WITH COLLEGE.

30:37.140 --> 30:39.244
DO YOU KNOW
WHERE YOU'RE GOING?

30:39.280 --> 30:41.009
I'M BEING TOTALLY BORING
AND GOING TO YALE.

30:41.040 --> 30:44.146
MY DAD CRIED WHEN
I GOT MY ACCEPTANCE LETTER.

30:44.180 --> 30:45.909
HE'S, LIKE,
A TOTAL DIE-HARD, SO...

30:45.940 --> 30:48.044
BUT WHAT ABOUT YOU?

30:48.080 --> 30:48.876
- I DON'T KNOW.

30:48.910 --> 30:50.423
- YOU, LIKE,
HAVEN'T DECIDED YET?

30:50.460 --> 30:51.973
- [sighs]

30:52.020 --> 30:53.942
- THIS GIRL'S
RIDICULOUSLY SMART.

30:53.990 --> 30:55.321
SHE'S, LIKE, STUPID SMART.
- ACTUALLY,

30:55.370 --> 30:57.509
IT'S JUST THAT
I DIDN'T GET INTO COLLEGE,

30:57.540 --> 30:59.599
TO ANY OF THE PLACES
THAT I APPLIED TO.

30:59.650 --> 31:01.299
SO IT'S NOT REALLY
THAT I HAVEN'T CHOSEN YET.

31:01.340 --> 31:02.955
IT'S MORE THAT
I DON'T HAVE ANY OPTIONS

31:02.990 --> 31:06.926
BECAUSE I DIDN'T GET IN.

31:06.960 --> 31:08.131
SORRY TO MAKE IT WEIRD.

31:08.170 --> 31:10.968
- I'M SO SORRY.

31:11.000 --> 31:13.059
THAT'S--

31:13.110 --> 31:14.964
THAT'S ACT UALLY--
YOU KNOW, THAT'S SO MUCH BETTER.

31:15.010 --> 31:17.149
'CAUSE NOW YOU CAN,
LIKE, DO WHATEVER YOU WANT.

31:17.180 --> 31:18.659
YOU KNOW, LIKE,
THE WORLD IS YOUR OYSTER.

31:18.700 --> 31:21.385
