THAT WAS A GREAT SAVE.

31:21.430 --> 31:24.012
I HOPE YOU HAVE
A GREAT LIFE AT COLLEGE

31:24.050 --> 31:25.119
AND A GREAT TIME
HERE AT PROM.

31:25.150 --> 31:26.424
CAN WE GO?
- SURE.

31:26.470 --> 31:28.153
- SEE YOU.

31:28.190 --> 31:30.112
- SEE YOU.
- SEE YOU.

31:30.160 --> 31:32.367
- BYE.
- SEE YOU, BYE.

31:32.400 --> 31:34.960
- HEY.
- HEY.

31:34.990 --> 31:37.094
- I'M KINDA FEELING SICK.
I DON'T KNOW WHAT IT IS.

31:37.130 --> 31:38.336
- YOU FEEL SICK?
- I DON'T WANT TO

31:38.370 --> 31:40.099
MAKE A BIG DEAL OUT OF IT,
BUT I THINK I MIGHT HAVE TO GO.

31:40.130 --> 31:41.643
JUST, LIKE,
MY STOMACH HURTS.

31:41.690 --> 31:43.089
- ARE YOU SURE?
ARE YOU OKAY?

31:43.140 --> 31:44.721
- I'M OKAY.
SO I'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW, OKAY?

31:44.760 --> 31:45.988
HAVE A GOOD TIME.
- YEAH.

31:46.040 --> 31:47.484
- SEE YOU IN A BIT.
- FEEL BETTER.

31:47.520 --> 31:50.102
- THANKS.
- ALL RIGHT, DUDE.

31:52.730 --> 31:54.106
- I DON'T KNOW.

32:10.610 --> 32:13.613
- [crying]

32:16.380 --> 32:19.417
[Darling I Doby Landon Pigg
and Lucy Schwartz]

32:29.360 --> 32:35.117
- GOLDEN LEAVES
LOOKED BROWN TO ME

32:35.160 --> 32:41.019
THE WORLD HAD LESS COLOR
WITHOUT YOU

32:41.060 --> 32:43.676
- SO...DO YOU THINK
THIS IS STUPID?

32:43.720 --> 32:46.291
DO YOU HATE IT
LIKE YOU THOUGHT?

32:46.340 --> 32:48.194
- IT WAS FUN.

32:48.240 --> 32:49.616
I LIKE SEEING YOU
ALL DRESSED UP.

32:49.650 --> 32:53.165
SO THANK YOU
FOR INVITING ME.

32:53.210 --> 32:56.304
- I KNOW...

32:56.350 --> 33:00.172
- UM...

33:00.210 --> 33:04.214
YOU KNOW HOW PEOPLE
KIND OF GET ROOMS AFTER?

33:04.250 --> 33:05.456
- YEAH.

33:05.500 --> 33:08.628
- UH...[chuckles]

33:08.670 --> 33:14.119
HAVE YOU...
EVER THOUGHT ABOUT THAT?

33:14.160 --> 33:18.813
- UM...

33:18.850 --> 33:20.431
WELL...

33:20.480 --> 33:23.688
YOU KNOW WHAT I THINK?

33:23.720 --> 33:26.097
WHEN THE TIME IS RIGHT...

33:26.140 --> 33:28.131
WE'RE GONNA KNOW IT.

33:28.170 --> 33:31.207
THERE IS NO RUSH.

33:31.250 --> 33:33.718
I'M NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

33:33.770 --> 33:38.309
- THEY DON'T SEE YOU
LIKE I DO

33:38.360 --> 33:41.181
DARLING I DO

33:41.220 --> 33:44.189
DARLING I DO

33:44.220 --> 33:47.326
SEE YOU

33:50.610 --> 33:53.261
DARLING I DO

33:53.300 --> 33:57.168
DARLING I DO

33:57.200 --> 33:59.134
IDO

33:59.170 --> 34:02.139
DARLING I DO

34:02.170 --> 34:04.752
DARLING I DO

34:04.800 --> 34:09.419
SEE YOU

34:09.460 --> 34:12.452
[keys clicking]

34:17.500 --> 34:20.492
[door closes]

34:20.540 --> 34:22.258
- HI.
- HEY.

34:22.300 --> 34:26.191
- YOU'RE HOME EARLY.

34:26.230 --> 34:27.811
- YEAH.
- WHAT HAPPENED?

34:27.850 --> 34:30.262
- NOTHING.
UH...I JUST--

34:30.300 --> 34:31.540
I DON'T WANT TO
TALK RIGHT NOW, OKAY?

34:31.580 --> 34:34.094
- OH, NO!
ARE YOU OKAY?

34:34.140 --> 34:35.471
- I'M FINE.
I JUST--

34:35.520 --> 34:37.238
I JUST DON'T WANT TO TALK,
OKAY?

34:37.280 --> 34:40.101
I JUST REALLY
DON'T WANT TO TALK.

34:40.140 --> 34:41.550
- WAS EVERYTHING
OKAY WITH THE DATE?

34:41.590 --> 34:43.694
- IT'S NOT ABOUT THAT.

34:43.730 --> 34:46.767
IT WAS FINE.
IT'S JUST...

34:46.800 --> 34:49.246
THIS WHOLE...

34:49.290 --> 34:51.281
THIS WHOLE THING
IS NOT WORKING.

34:51.330 --> 34:54.629
LIKE...
YOU KNOW,

34:54.670 --> 34:57.605
GOING TO HIGH SCHOOL
AND BEING A GREAT STUDENT

34:57.640 --> 35:00.268
AND GOING TO PROM
AND HAVING A NICE DATE

35:00.300 --> 35:01.153
AND GOING TO COLLEGE.

35:01.200 --> 35:03.122
LIKE, THAT'S JUST NOT
WORKING FOR ME.

35:03.170 --> 35:04.398
- OH, HONEY,
YOU'RE SO SMART.

35:04.440 --> 35:06.647
IT'S GONNA LOOK
DIFFERENT TOMORROW, YOU KNOW?

35:06.690 --> 35:08.612
IT'S JUST GONNA FEEL--
- MOM, CAN YOU JUST LISTEN!

35:08.650 --> 35:11.517
REALLY LISTEN TO WHAT
I'M SAYING, PLEASE!

35:11.550 --> 35:14.792
I AM TRYING TO COMMUNICATE
WITH YOU HONESTLY HERE, OKAY?

35:14.830 --> 35:19.244
I DID THE BEST I COULD
TO DO WHAT YOU WANT ME TO DO.

35:19.280 --> 35:22.283
I DID THE BEST THAT
I COULD TO BE GOOD IN SCHOOL,

35:22.320 --> 35:26.427
TO GO TO COLLEGE AND TAKE
PART IN THIS HIGH SCHOOL LIFE.

35:26.460 --> 35:27.939
BUT IT'S NOT WORKING
FOR ME.

35:27.980 --> 35:30.289
SO I'M SORRY,
BUT I NEED TO START DOING

35:30.330 --> 35:33.367
WHAT FEELS GOOD FOR ME
AND TRYING TO SEE IF THAT WORKS.

35:33.400 --> 35:34.958
BECAUSE THIS WHOLE THING

35:34.990 --> 35:36.742
OF DOING WHAT
YOU WANT ME TO DO

35:36.780 --> 35:38.224
AND WHAT YOU SUGGEST ME TO DO

35:38.270 --> 35:39.544
AND YOU TRYING
TO FIX MY PROBLEMS,

35:39.580 --> 35:40.740
IT'S NOT WORKING.

35:40.790 --> 35:42.712
IT'S NOT YOUR LIFE.
IT'S MY LIFE.

35:42.760 --> 35:44.546
AND I NEED YOU TO UNDERSTAND
THAT I'M GONNA START

35:44.590 --> 35:47.275
MAKING MY OWN DECISIONS,
WHETHER YOU LIKE THEM OR NOT.

35:47.310 --> 35:48.550
AND THAT HAS
TO BE OKAY WITH YOU,

35:48.590 --> 35:50.865
BECAUSE IT'S WHO I AM.

35:50.900 --> 35:52.481
OKAY?

36:12.270 --> 36:15.683
- ALEX.
- YES?

36:15.720 --> 36:18.757
- REMEMBER WHEN
YOU WERE TALKING ABOUT,

36:18.790 --> 36:22.203
LIKE, TIME?

36:22.240 --> 36:25.346
- YEAH?
- AND, LIKE, UM...

36:25.390 --> 36:30.453
WHEN THE TIME IS RIGHT, THEN--
THAT WE'LL KNOW.

36:30.490 --> 36:33.288
- YEAH?

36:33.320 --> 36:39.805
- I FEEL LIKE RIGHT NOW
IS THE RIGHT TIME.

36:39.850 --> 36:41.704
- HADDIE, I DON'T
WANT YOU TO FEEL PRESSURE

36:41.750 --> 36:43.365
JUST BECAUSE,
YOU KNOW, IT'S PROM NIGHT

36:43.400 --> 36:45.027
AND YOUR FRIENDS GOT ROOMS.

36:45.060 --> 36:46.027
- NO, I DON'T.

36:46.060 --> 36:48.927
I FEEL--I FEEL LIKE
THIS IS THE RIGHT TIME.

36:48.960 --> 36:52.782
I FEEL GOOD.

36:52.830 --> 36:55.515
- I FEEL GOOD.
- OKAY.

36:55.550 --> 36:58.553
- MM-HMM.

37:21.890 --> 37:23.778
- HONEY, I'M REALLY
STARTING TO WORRY.

37:23.820 --> 37:25.469
- WHY?
- BECAUSE SHE--

37:25.510 --> 37:27.307
LOOK, IT'S FOUR MINUTES
UNTIL CURFEW.

37:27.340 --> 37:29.479
- SHE HAS FOUR MINUTES.
- I'M GONNA GIVE HER A CALL.

37:29.520 --> 37:30.475
JUST GONNA MAKE SURE SHE'S--
- HONEY.

37:30.520 --> 37:31.964
- WHAT?
- STOP PANICKING.

37:32.000 --> 37:33.627
- I'M NOT PANICKING.
- YOU ARE PANICKING.

37:33.660 --> 37:35.582
- I'M NOT.
- YES, YOU ARE.

37:35.630 --> 37:37.416
[door opens]

37:37.460 --> 37:39.621
- AH.

37:39.670 --> 37:42.662
- SEE?

37:48.640 --> 37:50.847
HEY.

37:50.880 --> 37:52.086
- HEY.
- HEY, SWEETIE.

37:52.130 --> 37:54.598
- HOW'D IT GO?
- DID YOU HAVE A GOOD TIME?

37:54.650 --> 37:55.742
- YEAH.

37:55.790 --> 37:57.929
YEAH, IT WAS REALLY GOOD.

37:57.960 --> 38:00.611
JENNA WAS PROM QUEEN

38:00.650 --> 38:03.517
AND THE DECORATIONS
LOOKED REALLY NICE, SO...

38:04.590 --> 38:06.444
YEAH, I'M GONNA GO TO BED.
- GREAT.

38:06.490 --> 38:08.105
- I'M TIRED.
- OKAY.

38:08.140 --> 38:09.516
- YOU CAN SLEEP IN
TOMORROW IF YOU WANT.

38:09.560 --> 38:12.347
- HEY, THANK YOU
FOR MAKING CURFEW.

38:12.390 --> 38:14.836
- UM...THANKS FOR
THE DRESS.

38:14.870 --> 38:17.316
both: YOU'RE WELCOME.

38:23.920 --> 38:25.319
- FEEL BETTER?

38:25.370 --> 38:26.576
- YES.
YES, I DO.

38:28.720 --> 38:31.678
SHE'S A GOOD GIRL.
- YES, SHE IS.

38:57.470 --> 39:00.439
- FOR WHAT IT'S WORTH...

39:00.470 --> 39:04.531
I'VE ALWAYS WANTED
TO PLAY GOLF WITH YOU.

39:04.580 --> 39:05.808
- [sighs]

39:05.860 --> 39:09.569
- SOMEONE

39:09.620 --> 39:11.588
- [crying]

39:11.620 --> 39:15.579
- REACHING FOR ME NOW

39:15.620 --> 39:18.862
- I LOVE YOU SO MUCH.

39:20.560 --> 39:26.692
- THROUGH THE DARK

39:26.740 --> 39:29.732
REACHING FOR ME NOW

39:36.440 --> 39:39.477
YOU NEED

39:39.510 --> 39:41.717
SOMEONE

39:41.750 --> 39:45.470
TO HEAR YOU WHEN YOU SIGH

39:45.520 --> 39:46.828
[door closes]

39:51.630 --> 39:55.452
SOMEONE

39:55.490 --> 40:00.666
TO WIPE AWAY THOSE TEARS
YOU CRY

40:06.880 --> 40:09.121
- WOW, SOMEBODY
REALLY LIKED CATS.

40:09.160 --> 40:10.775
- MOLDY, EVEN.

40:10.820 --> 40:12.708
CLEARLY, THE WINDOWS
HAVE TO COME OUT.

40:12.750 --> 40:13.842
- YEAH.

40:13.890 --> 40:15.505
- THAT'S NOT TOO HARD,
THOUGH, IS IT?

40:15.550 --> 40:17.711
- NO, I MEAN,
IT'S NOT TOO HARD,

40:17.760 --> 40:20.923
BUT WHEN YOU ADD THAT
TO THE KITCHEN CABINETS

40:20.970 --> 40:24.098
AND THE TILES AND
THE AROMA OF ALLEGED HOMICIDE,

40:24.140 --> 40:26.108
IT'S NOT NOTHING, MAN.
- ALL RIGHT.

40:26.140 --> 40:27.448
- CROS,
HAVE YOU CHECKED OUT

40:27.490 --> 40:29.071
THIS LITTLE HOUSE
ACROSS THE STREET?

40:29.110 --> 40:30.691
IT'S REALLY CUTE.
- YEAH.

40:30.730 --> 40:32.732
OBVIOUSLY, IF I COULD
AFFORD THE PERFECT HOUSE

40:32.770 --> 40:34.499
ACROSS THE STREET,
I WOULD'VE GOT THAT ONE.

40:34.530 --> 40:36.737
I'M NOT AN IDIOT.

40:36.770 --> 40:38.738
- CROS, THAT'S NOT
WHAT I WAS SAYING AT ALL.

40:38.780 --> 40:41.669
THIS IS A REALLY SWEET IDEA.
- SUCH A NICE IDEA.

40:41.710 --> 40:42.984
- IT'S JUST
IT'S A LOT OF MONEY

40:43.020 --> 40:44.988
AND A LOT
OF RESPONSIBILITY.

40:45.020 --> 40:47.056
- WELL, I ALREADY
BOUGHT THIS HOUSE, SO...

40:50.620 --> 40:53.578
- THIS ONE?

40:53.620 --> 40:55.099
- OH.

40:55.140 --> 40:57.791
OH, MY GOD.

40:57.830 --> 41:02.073
OH, MY GOD, I DO NOT
KNOW WHAT I WAS THINKING.

41:02.110 --> 41:04.590
I MEAN, ACTUALLY I DO.
I WAS THINKING,

41:04.630 --> 41:06.109
"YOU KNOW,
I ALREADY WRECKED MY LIFE,

41:06.150 --> 41:08.072
"SO I DON'T REALLY CARE
IF I WRECK IT WORSE

41:08.120 --> 41:11.704
BECAUSE YOU CAN'T REALLY
WRECK IT WORSE THAN TOTALLY."

41:11.740 --> 41:13.708
- THAT'S NOT TRUE.
- THERE'S CONTINGENCIES HERE.

41:13.740 --> 41:15.492
- YEAH, THE INSPECTION
MIGHT NOT GO THROUGH.

41:15.540 --> 41:16.393
- NOT A CHANCE.
- YEAH.

41:16.430 --> 41:18.603
YOU CAN WIGGLE
OUT OF IT DURING ESCROW.

41:18.640 --> 41:21.814
- YEAH, WELL, I ALREADY
SOLD THE HOUSE BOAT.

41:23.750 --> 41:24.956
- HE DID.

41:24.990 --> 41:26.685
- WOW.

41:26.720 --> 41:30.781
- IT SEEMED LIKE A GROWN-UP
THING TO DO AT THE TIME.

41:30.830 --> 41:32.923
- WELL, IT WAS.

41:32.970 --> 41:34.938
I MEAN, WHAT KIND
OF A GROWN-UP GUY

41:34.970 --> 41:38.861
LIVES ON A HOUSE BOAT?

41:38.910 --> 41:41.902
- THANKS FOR COMING.

41:43.700 --> 41:46.214
- I MEAN, NOT THAT
THIS PLACE ISN'T A DUMP.

41:46.260 --> 41:47.943
- AWFUL.
- [chuckles]

41:47.980 --> 41:51.154
- [laughing]

41:51.190 --> 41:52.987
YOU THINK I CAN FIX IT?

41:54.990 --> 41:57.299
- NO.
- OKAY. GREAT.

41:57.340 --> 42:00.503
- I THINK WE CAN FIX IT.

42:07.900 --> 42:09.652
- SORRY.

42:11.800 --> 42:12.937
- YEAH, YEAH.

42:12.970 --> 42:14.176
- I BOUGHT A BAD HOUSE.

42:14.220 --> 42:17.007
[indistinct chatter]
